gw.api.admin

Class EventMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.admin.EventMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.service.data.Idable, Serializable

    public class EventMessage
extends Object
implements com.guidewire.pl.system.service.data.Idable, Serializable
    Information about a single message in the Guidewire messaging system (see the Integration Guide for details of messaging). Each EventMessage object represents details of a message:
    • The message id
    • Whether the message can be skipped. Only active messages - messages which haven't already been processed - can be skipped.
    • The message send time.
    • The message name.
    • The message destination id.
    • The message destination name.
    • The message order (messages are sent in the order they were added).
    • The message sender reference (an optional field, set at send time by some messaging plugins).
    • The message status (for example Pending Send, Acknowledged).
    • The message response - set to an error message if the message failed, otherwise empty.
    EventMessage objects are used to display a snapshot of the status of individual messages in the administration UI.
